getBSCObject

public BSCObject getBSCObject(java.lang.String URIstring)
Retrieve a single BSC object from the model. The URI for the object can be specified as either a full URI or with a short-form prefix.

Parameters:
URIstring - The URI for an object to get from the model.
Returns:
The specified object if it exists, null otherwise.

getRDFStatements

public RDFStatementIter getRDFStatements()
Get an iterator for all RDF statements in the model. The is essentially the same as listStatements() for Jena models, except that subjects and objects of statements are returned as BSCObjects. This is probably not very useful in most cases because even simple models will include many statements if they reference external RDF sources.

Returns:
An iterator for all model statements.

An iterator for the query results.

getDefaultPrefixMap

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getDefaultPrefixMap()
Builds and returns the default prefix map for BSC models. Note that RDF data sources can specify their own prefix mappings in addition to the default mapping.

Returns:
The default prefix map.
